SECOND REGULAR SESSION
HOUSE BILL NO. 3327
103RD GENERAL ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY REPRESENTATIVE KEATHLEY.
7145H.01I JOSEPH ENGLER, Chief Clerk
AN ACT
To amend chapter 311, RSMo, by adding thereto one new section relating to the establishment
of certain entertainment districts.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the state of Missouri, as follows:
Section A. Chapter 311, RSMo, is amended by adding thereto one new section, to be
2 known as section 311.083, to read as follows:
311.083. 1. As used in this section, the following terms mean:
2 (1) "Common area", any public area within an entertainment district and any
3 area of a public right-of-way that is within the entertainment district. "Common area"
4 shall not include areas open to the public that are located within an establishment
5 licensed under this chapter;
6 (2) "Entertainment district", any area in any county bordering the Missouri
7 river, and that:
8 (a) Is located in any city with more than forty-six thousand but fewer than fifty-
9 one thousand inhabitants;
10 (b) Contains a combination of entertainment venues, bars, nightclubs,
11 restaurants, and other licensed establishments and common areas; and
12 (c) Is designated as such by an ordinance of the governing body of the city;
13 (3) "Portable bar", any bar, table, kiosk, cart, or stand that is not a permanent
14 fixture and can be moved from place to place.
15 2. Notwithstanding any other provisions of this chapter to the contrary, any
16 person who possesses the qualifications required under this chapter, and who meets the
17 requirements of and complies with the provisions of this chapter, may apply for, and the
EXPLANATION — Matter enclosed in bold-faced brackets [thus] in the above bill is not enacted and is
intended to be omitted from the law. Matter in bold-face type in the above bill is proposed language.

HB 3327 2
18 supervisor of alcohol and tobacco control may issue, an entertainment district special
19 license to sell intoxicating liquor by the drink for retail for consumption dispensed from
20 one or more licensed establishments including, but not limited to, portable bars within
21 the entertainment district, until 1:30 a.m. on Mondays through Saturdays and from 6:00
22 a.m. on Sundays and until 1:30 a.m. on Mondays.
23 3. An applicant granted an entertainment district special license under this
24 section shall pay a license fee of three hundred dollars per year.
25 4. Notwithstanding any other provision of this chapter to the contrary, on such
26 days and at such times during the hours a licensee is allowed under this chapter to sell
27 alcoholic beverages, licensed establishments holding an entertainment district special
28 license under this section may allow persons to leave the licensed premises located in
29 portions of the entertainment district with an alcoholic beverage and enter upon and
30 consume the alcoholic beverage within other licensed establishments and common areas
31 located in portions of the entertainment district. No person shall take any alcoholic
32 beverage or alcoholic beverages outside the boundaries of the entertainment district.
33 5. Every licensee within the entertainment district shall serve alcoholic
34 beverages in containers that display and contain the licensee's trade name or logo or
35 some other mark that is unique to that license and licensee.
36 6. The holder of an entertainment district special license is solely responsible for
37 alcohol violations occurring on its premises, including any portable bar, and in any
38 common area.
39 7. The governing body of the city in which the entertainment district is located
40 shall be authorized to adopt by ordinance procedures for approval or rejection of such
41 entertainment districts as well as rules and regulations for conduct and enforcement
42 thereof consistent with this section.
